@kangkaisen 
Is there any benchmark for `std::stoul`, better to create an issue to trace this problem. It will also be useful for others

@imay OK, `:` is good.
So we can handle `/home/disk1/palo.HDD, 50`,`/home/disk1/palo, capacity:50, medium: HDD`.
But how to do with `/home/disk1/palo.HDD, capacity:50, medium:SSD`?

@vagetablechicken 

> But how to do with `/home/disk1/palo.HDD, capacity:50, medium:SSD`?

For this case, property `medium` has a higher priority. Otherwise, the medium can not be specified except changing directory name.

@vagetablechicken 

1. I think meta tool should not care about the medium of data path.
2. Even if meta tool care about medium, it is better to make medium and capacity parse in one place. You can make config parse a function, which can be called by both options and meta dir.

@caiconghui 

I have see your PR for this patch. This is one way to make thing work.
And is it easy to let show create table return column defination without REPLACE?

There are two flag bits for Issue #2245, 

- one for set the default rowset type to BETA; 

- one for set the default compaction type to BETA.

@caiconghui 

Now we have no restrict on key columns and value columns. So it is OK to make all columns nullable default.
And if we support primary key in the future, then we should make key not nullable.
